# Review Checklist

## Purpose

Standardize review quality for human and AI reviewers.

## When It Applies

Before merging any PR or marking a sprint task complete.

## Requirements

- [ ] Scope matches PRD/sprint task — no unrelated changes
- [ ] Layer boundaries respected (no SDK leaks)
- [ ] Types exported from `@repo/types` where shared
- [ ] Errors use `BaseError`; API uses `ApiResponse` envelope
- [ ] Env vars documented in `.env.example` if added
- [ ] Docs updated (API.md, ARCHITECTURE.md, etc.) if behavior changed
- [ ] `pnpm lint` and `pnpm build` pass
- [ ] No secrets committed
- [ ] Accessibility basics (labels, keyboard) for new UI

## Examples

```
✅ PR adds UserService + tests + updates docs/API.md
✅ PR notes "Out of scope: auth middleware (Sprint 4)"
```

## Bad Examples

```
❌ PR adds Supabase SDK to apps/web without adapter layer
❌ PR changes 20 files but description says "small fix"
❌ PR merges with failing build "will fix later"
```
